==English==

===Noun===

'''meander'''

#A winding, crooked, or involved course; as, the meanders of the veins and arteries.
#A tortuous or intricate movement.
#Fretwork. See Fret.

===Verb===

'''to meander'''

#To [[wind]], [[turn]], or [[twist]]; to make [[flexuous]]; to [[wander]]
#:''The stream '''meandered''' through the valley.''

